The sleep statement is used to delay the execution of a statement or block of statements for a specified amount of time (in milliseconds). It allows you to easily add pauses into your code without having to write complex logic for each one. For example, when you want to wait for 1 second before continuing with your application, just use this syntax:
sleep(1000);
Or when you want to wait for 3 seconds between two statements, use this syntax instead:
sleep(3000);
